        <briefdescription>
<para>Test if the backend supports alternate screen buffer codes. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If this method returns <computeroutput>true</computeroutput>, the ANSI codes <computeroutput>ESC[?1049h</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>ESC[?1049l</computeroutput> are sent to the backend to switch to the alternate screen buffer. <emphasis>Additionally</emphasis> <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_backend_1a36c61941344560b8dfa1ec97ae216cad" kindref="member">setAlternateScreenBuffer()</ref></computeroutput> is called to notify the backend about the change. If this method returns <computeroutput>false</computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_terminal" kindref="compound">Terminal</ref></computeroutput> <emphasis>only</emphasis> calls <computeroutput><ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1_backend_1a36c61941344560b8dfa1ec97ae216cad" kindref="member">setAlternateScreenBuffer()</ref></computeroutput> instead. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
